:Dii is also the plural of Latin Deus.''


The 'Dii' (; ) were an independent Thracian tribe, swordsmen, who lived among
the foothills of Mount Rhodope in Thrace. They often joined the ranks of
organized armies as mercenaries or volunteers. Thucydides declared that they
were the most warlike infantry in Sitalkes' army.

Though usually described as swordsmen, they defeated a Theban cavalry by
using peltast tactics, so they were certainly skilled in other areas of
warfare as well.

The Legend of Diyes is an interesting legend about the Dii.
